          <div data-content-element-selector="p, .js-buylink-item-container" data-allowed-classes-selector="js-buylink-item-container">
                <p>Everybody likes free games, and <a href="https://www.gog.com/en/game/warhammer_40000_gladius_relics_of_war" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">GOG.com</a> is offering <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/games/warhammer-40000-gladius-relics-of-war/">Warhammer 40,000: Gladius - Relics of War</a> for free, but only for a limited time. Usually priced at $40, the offer expires on June 18, so if you want to dive into some Warhammer fun for free, grab it before it's too late.</p><p>On top of that, GOG is offering several DLC packs on sale for 25-76% off, with prices ranging from $1.67-$11.24. Upon release, the game received mixed reviews, with <a href="https://www.metacritic.com/game/warhammer-40000-gladius-relics-of-war/" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener">most of the praise</a> centered around the polished combat improvements from previous installments.</p><figure data-align="center" data-size="large" data-img-src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1597/15976769/4510823-jzgwdo4rlaffb9byrc6ca.jpg" data-ref-id="1300-4510823" data-ratio="0.5625" data-width="1280" data-embed-type="image"><a href="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1597/15976769/4510823-jzgwdo4rlaffb9byrc6ca.jpg" data-ref-id="1300-4510823"></a><figcaption>Warhammer 40,000: Gladius - Relics of War</figcaption><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1597/15976769/4510823-jzgwdo4rlaffb9byrc6ca.jpg"></figure><p>"Gladius Prime was known to Imperial scholars as a planet of archeological interest. During its colonization, ancient relics were found, revealing hints of a shrouded past," the official synopsis reads. "But it was more than relics. Something awakened, an unspeakable horror from an ancient past, and the citizens of Gladius found themselves trapped in a terrible war for survival. Gladius Prime was once a planet of peace. Now there is only war."</p><p>The game features four factions taking on one another in a brutal war for dominance over the planet's resources: Astra Militarum, Space Marines, Orks, and Necrons. Much like the tabletop equivalent, each group has its own unique gameplay, technological tree, units, and heroes.</p><p>If you're looking for more Warhammer 40K games, GOG has a $20 bundle of three Warhammer games, usually priced at $100. If tactical RPGs aren't your thing, Steam has a more family-friendly game full of multiplayer mayhem that's <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/theres-a-free-game-on-steam-for-a-limited-time-that-lets-you-lick-your-friends/1100-6532317/" data-ref-id="1100-6532317">also free for a limited time</a>. </p>
  
                        
    
        
        
  
